message.content:
Fix text shape hit-testing in the collaborative whiteboard at C:/Users/sahil/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/Mechanize_takehome/.

Read client/src/canvasRenderer.ts first.

**Problem:** Text shapes have approximate width calculated as `text.length * fontSize * 0.6` when created, which doesn't match actual rendered glyph widths. Hit testing uses this stored width, so clicks can miss or falsely hit text shapes.

**Fix in canvasRenderer.ts:**

1. In the `drawShape` function, for the "text" case: after drawing the text, update the shape's width to match the actual measured width. Use `ctx.measureText(shape.text || "").width`. Since Shape is passed by reference from the shapes array, mutating `shape.width` here will update the scene graph for accurate hit testing:

```typescript
case "text": {
  const fontSize = shape.fontSize || 16;
  ctx.font = `${fontSize}px sans-serif`;
  const measured = ctx.measureText(shape.text || "");
  // Update stored width to match actual rendered width for hit-testing
  shape.width = measured.width;
  shape.height = fontSize * 1.2; // line height
  ctx.fillStyle = shape.fill || "#000000";
  ctx.fillText(shape.text || "", shape.x, shape.y + fontSize);
  // ... rest of text rendering
}
```

2. Also update the `isPointInShape` function for the "text" case — it already uses the bounding box check which will now be accurate since we fixed the width.

That's it. Small surgical change. Don't touch any other files.

